{
"id": 6589,
"documentId": "p97hxig6wabkizw2as3eouxo",
"title": "وقال عليه السلام لنا حقّ فإن أُعطيناه وإلّا ركبنا أعجاز الإبل وإن طال السُّرى. وهذا من لطيف الكلام وفصيحه ومعناه أنّا إن لم نُعطَ حقّنا كنّا أذلّاء وذلك أنّ الرديف يركب عَجُز البعير كالعبد والأسير ومن يجري مجراهما.",
"slug": "we-have-a-right-if-it-is-given-to-us-good-if-not-we-will-ride-the-camel-s-rump-through-the-long-nigh",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:00:58.180Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:00:58.180Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:00:58.208Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "We have a right. If it is given to us, good. If not, we will ride the camel’s rump through the long night. Raḍī: This statement is among the most refined and eloquent of expressions, and it means that when we are not given our due, we are being dishonored; that is because a pillion rider rides on the camel’s rump, as does a slave, or captive, or another person of lowly status.",
"type": "en"
}
],
"sermonNumber": "3.17",
