"arabic_word": "",
"english_word": "responded",
"arabic_interpretation": "",
"english_translation": "In 36/656, during the march toward Ṣiffīn. Anbar is in northern Iraq, and the merchant family is named as the Banū Khushnūshak (Persian name). Text and context in Minqarī, Waqʿat Ṣiffīn, 143-144.",
