{
"id": 6621,
"documentId": "bbvq0powxmy51b6c6zqlfwt2",
"title": "وقال لٱبنه الحسن عليهما السلام يا بُنَيّ ٱحفظ عنّي أربعًا وأربعًا لا يضرّك ما عملتَ معهنّ إنّ أغنى الغنى العقل وأكبر الفقر الحُمق وأوحش الوحشة العُجب وأكرم الحسب حسن الخلق. يا بُنَيّ إيّاك ومُصادقةَ الأحمق فإنّه يريد أن ينفعك فيضرّك وإيّاك ومصادقة البخيل فإنّه يَقعُد عنك أَحْوَج ما تكون إليه وإيّاك ومصادقة الفاجر فإنّه يبيعك بالتافِه وإيّاك ومصادقة الكذّاب فإنّه كالسَّراب يقرّب عليك البعيد ويُبعد عليك القريب.",
"slug": "warning-to-asan-about-whom-not-to-befriend",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:07.583Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:07.583Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:07.602Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "ʿAlī said to his son Ḥasan: My dear son, remember four things from me, and four things more—nothing will harm you as long as you follow them. The best wealth is intelligence, the greatest poverty is foolishness, the loneliest alienation comes from conceit, and the noblest lineage is good character. My dear son, beware of befriending a fool—he wants to help you but will harm you. Beware of befriending a miser—he will hold back from helping you when you need him most. Beware of befriending a wanton—he will sell you out for a trifle. Beware of befriending a liar—he is like a mirage that makes near what is distant and makes distant what is near.",
"type": "en"
}
],
"sermonNumber": "3.33",
"heading": "Warning to Ḥasan about whom not to befriend",
