{
"id": 6695,
"documentId": "vabsaduvgdzmxdnbyxqblb8k",
"title": "ومن كلام له عليه السلام للشاميّ لمّا سأله أكان مسيره إلى الشام بقضاء من الله وقدر بعد كلام طويل هذا مختاره وَيحَك لعلّك ظننت قضاء لازمًا وقَدَرًا حاتمًا. ولو كان كذلك لبطل الثواب والعقاب وسقط الوعد والوعيد. إنّ الله سبحانه أمر عباده تخييرًا ونهاهم تحذيرًا وكلّف يسيرًا ولم يكلّف عسيرًا وأعطى على القليل كثيرًا. ولم يُعصَ مغلوبًا ولم يُطَع مكرِهًا ولم يرسل الأنبياء لَعِبًا ولم ينزل الكتب للعباد عبثًا ولا خلق السماوات ﴿وَٱلْأَرْضَ وَمَا بَيْنَهُمَا بَاطِلًا ذَٰلِكَ ظَنُّ ٱلَّذِينَ كَفَرُوْا فَوَيْلٌ لِّلَّذِينَ كَفَرُوْا مِنَ ٱلنَّارِ﴾.",
"slug": "destiny-and-the-march-on-syria",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:25.983Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:25.983Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:25.995Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "From ʿAlī’s words to the Syrian who asked whether the march on Syria was decreed by God. ʿAlī gave a lengthy answer from which the following is a selection:Woe! Perhaps you think destiny is final and fate absolute! If that were the case, God’s reward and punishment would be invalid, and God’s promise and threat would have no meaning. God has commanded his servants to do certain things, while giving them free choice, and forbidden them from doing other things, while giving them fair warning. He has imposed on them easy, not harsh tasks, and has promised great rewards for small efforts. When he is disobeyed, it is not because he is overpowered. When he is obeyed, it is not because he coerced. He has not sent prophets in play, or revealed scriptures on a whim, or created the skies «and the earth in vain. That is the claim of those who do not believe—woe and hellfire to unbelievers!»",
"type": "en"
}
],
"sermonNumber": "3.70",
"heading": "Destiny and the march on Syria",
