{
"id": 6697,
"documentId": "c1th1lhu34qg7bve4rw4pyyi",
"title": "وقال عليه السلام خذ الحكمة أَنّٰى كانت فإنّ الحكمة تكون في صدر المنافق فتَلَجلَجُ في صدره حتّى تَخرج فتسكن إلى صواحبها في صدر المؤمن. وقال عليه السلام في مثل ذلك الحكمة ضالّة المؤمن فخذ الحكمة ولو من أهل النفاق.",
"slug": "seize-wisdom-wherever-you-find-it-a-wise-maxim-may-reside-in-the-breast-of-a-hypocrite-and-it-quiver",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:26.452Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:26.452Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:26.465Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "Seize wisdom wherever you find it. A wise maxim may reside in the breast of a hypocrite, and it quivers and trembles there until it settles next to its kin, in the breast of a believer. ʿAlī also said in a similar vein: Believers, wisdom is your own lost camel—seize it, then, even from hypocrites!",
"type": "en"
}
],
