{
"id": 6723,
"documentId": "eqqcqbusmaa4o7cu7993esjq",
"title": "وقال عليه السلام لا يقولنّ أحدكم ٱللّٰهم إنّي أعوذ بك من الفتنة لأنّه ليس أحد إلّا وهو مشتمل على فتنة ولكن من ٱستعاذ فليستعذ من مُضِلّات الفتن فإنّ الله سبحانه يقول ﴿وَٱعْلَمُوٓاْ أَنَّمَآ أَمْوَالُكُمْ وَأَوْلَادُكُمْ فِتْنَةٌ﴾. ومعنى ذلك أنّه سبحانه يختبرهم بالأموال والأولاد ليتبيّن الساخط لرزقه والراضي بقِسمه وإن كان سبحانه أعلم بهم من أنفسهم ولكن لتظهر الأفعال التي بها يُستحَقّ الثواب والعقاب لأنّ بعضهم يحبّ الذُّكور ويكره الإناث وبعضهم يحبّ تثمير المال ويكره ٱنثلام الحال. وهذا من غريب ما سمع منه عليه السلام في التفسير.",
"slug": "never-say-god-protect-me-from-trial-for-no-one-is-free-from-exposure-to-trial-if-you-wish-to-seek-go",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:32.959Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:32.959Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:32.974Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "Never say, “God, protect me from trial!” for no one is free from exposure to trial. If you wish to seek God’s protection, seek it against the inducements to stray that occur during times of trial. God has said, «Know that the riches you own and the children you beget are nothing but trials!» This means that the Almighty tests people through wealth and children to see who is unhappy with his lot and who accepts his share with equanimity. The Almighty knows what is in their hearts more than they do, but the trials prompt them to actions by which they earn either reward or punishment. Some prefer male children and dislike girls. Others are obsessed with amassing wealth and lose patience when their robes fray. Raḍī: This is among the wondrous commentaries on the Qurʾan heard from ʿAlī.",
"type": "en"
}
],
"sermonNumber": "3.84",
"heading": "Never say, “God, protect me from trial!” for no one is free from exposure to trial. If you wish to seek God’s protection,",
"footnotes": [
{
"id": 1642,
"documentId": "tb951c3nq9f1vcp0v33t0o3b",
"number": "827",
"section": "3.84",
"arabic_word": "",
"english_word": "trials",
"arabic_interpretation": "",
"english_translation": "Qurʾan, Anfāl 8:28.",
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:47.405Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:47.405Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:47.434Z"
}
],
"paragraphs": []
},
{
"id": 6725,
"documentId": "xhp7gpshj4azzznmemxqsmx7",
"title": "وسئل عليه السلام عن الخير ما هو فقال ليس الخير أن يكثر مالك وولدك ولكنّ الخير أن يكثر علمك وأن يعظم حلمك وأن تُباهي الناس بعبادة ربّك فإن أحسنتَ حمدتَ الله وإن أسأت ٱستغفرت الله. ولا خير في الدنيا إلّا لرجلين رجل أذنب ذنوبًا فهو يتداركها بالتوبة ورجل يسارع في الخيرات. ولا يقلّ عمل مع التقوى وكيف يَقلّ ما يُتقبَّل.",
"slug": "al-was-asked-what-constitutes-distinction-and-he-replied",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:33.453Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:33.453Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:33.463Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "ʿAlī was asked, “What constitutes distinction?” and he replied: Possessing great wealth and having many children are not marks of distinction—distinction is obtained through vast knowledge and abundant kindness, and by vying to worship the Lord. If you do good, praise God, if you do ill, beg his forgiveness. Distinction in this world is reserved for two kinds of men: one who commits a sin but atones for it by repenting, and one who hastens to perform good deeds. No deed is too small if performed with piety—how can something that God accepts ever be small?",
"type": "en"
}
],
"sermonNumber": "3.85",
"heading": "ʿAlī was asked, “What constitutes distinction?” and he replied:",
"footnotes": [],
"paragraphs": []
},
{
"id": 6727,
"documentId": "pirpbijbe5q6y49smvypboe2",
"title": "وقال عليه السلام إنّ أَولى الناس بالأنبياء أعلمهم بما جاءوا به ثمّ تلى عليه السلام ﴿إِنَّ أَوْلَى النَّاسِ بِإِبْرَاهِيمَ لَلَّذِينَ اتَّبَعُوهُ وَهَٰذَا النَّبِيُّ وَالَّذِينَ آمَنُوا وَاللَّهُ وَلِيُّ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ﴾ ثم قال عليه السلام إنّ وليّ محمّد من أطاع الله وإن بعدت لُحْمَته وإنّ عدوّ محمّد من عصى الله وإن قربت قرابته.",
"slug": "al-said-closest-to-prophets-are-those-who-discern-their-message-best",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:33.947Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:33.947Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:33.998Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "ʿAlī said: Closest to prophets are those who discern their message best. Then he recited, «Closest to Abraham are those who followed him, as is this Prophet, and those who profess belief—God is close to believers.» Then he continued: One who obeys God is Muḥammad’s kinsman, however distant he may be in bloodline. One who disobeys God is Muḥammad’s enemy, however close he may be in kinship.",
"type": "en"
}
],
"sermonNumber": "3.86",
"heading": "ʿAlī said: Closest to prophets are those who discern their message best.",
"footnotes": [
{
"id": 1644,
"documentId": "kn5fsmrrp61xp7yqyoipzowo",
"number": "828",
"section": "3.86",
"arabic_word": "",
"english_word": "believers",
"arabic_interpretation": "",
"english_translation": "Qurʾan, Āl ʿImrān 3:68.",
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:47.812Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:47.812Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:47.831Z"
}
],
"paragraphs": []
},
{
"id": 6729,
"documentId": "l0u2prlye4zawgybku4hm9tr",
"title": "وقال عليه السلام وقد سمع رجلًا من الحَروريّة يتهجّد ويقرأ نوم على يقين خير من صلاة في شكّ.",
"slug": "al-heard-a-ar-r-kharijite-praying-late-in-the-night-and-reciting-the-qur-an-and-he-said",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:34.688Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:34.688Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:34.698Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "ʿAlī heard a Ḥarūrī Kharijite praying late in the night and reciting the Qurʾan, and he said: Sleep accompanied by certainty is better than prayer accompanied by doubt.",
"type": "en"
}
],
"sermonNumber": "3.87",
"heading": "ʿAlī heard a Ḥarūrī Kharijite praying late in the night and reciting the Qurʾan, and he said:",
"footnotes": [
{
"id": 1646,
"documentId": "f6nx4gd1jjj7d08422x2m7o8",
"number": "829",
"section": "3.87",
"arabic_word": "",
"english_word": "said",
"arabic_interpretation": "",
"english_translation": "Presumably in Kufa, soon after the Kharijites’ secession in 37/658. The Ḥarūriyyah were the first Kharijites—Ḥarūrāʾ was the place near Kufa where they initially gathered to protest against ʿAlī",
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:48.220Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:48.220Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:48.235Z"
}
],
"paragraphs": []
},
{
"id": 6731,
"documentId": "j9fvcqjk2lc6xd0evkxawa5a",
"title": "وقال عليه السلام اِعقِلوا الخبر إذا سمعتموه عقل رعاية لا عقل رواية فإنّ رواة العلم كثير ورعاته قليل.",
"slug": "study-any-hadith-you-hear-with-mindful-attention-not-by-rote-learning-narrators-of-knowledge-are-man",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:35.159Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:35.159Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:35.169Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "Study any hadith you hear with mindful attention, not by rote learning. Narrators of knowledge are many, its true custodians few.",
"type": "en"
}
],
"sermonNumber": "3.88",
"heading": "Study any hadith you hear with mindful attention, not by rote learning. Narrators of knowledge are many, its true custodians few.",
"footnotes": [
{
"id": 1648,
"documentId": "ri8v9aq62rsnsm65dlvi5z7h",
"number": "830",
"section": "3.88",
"arabic_word": "",
"english_word": "learning",
"arabic_interpretation": "",
"english_translation": "Ar. khabar, lit. “report,” translated here as “hadith.” The last lines of §1.236 are similar.",
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:48.620Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:48.620Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:48.645Z"
}
],
