},
{
"id": 6733,
"documentId": "gjkdxtgbezp6mimtygo38118",
"title": "وقال عليه السلام وقد سمع رجلًا يقول ﴿إِنَّا لِلّٰهِ وَإِنَّآ إِلَيْهِ رَاجِعُوْنَ﴾ إنّ قولنا ﴿إِنَّا لِلّٰهِ﴾ إقرار على أنفسنا بالمُلك. وقولنا ﴿وَإِنَّآ إِلَيْهِ رَاجِعُوْن﴾ إقرار على أنفسنا بالهُلك.",
"slug": "al-heard-a-man-intone-to-god-we-belong-and-to-him-we-shall-return-and-he-said",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:35.836Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:35.836Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:35.853Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "3.89 ʿAlī heard a man intone, «To God we belong and to him we shall return!» and he said: When we say, «To God we belong,» we acknowledge our subjugation. When we say, «To him we shall return,» we acknowledge our mortality.",
"type": "en"
}
],
"sermonNumber": "3.89",
"heading": "ʿAlī heard a man intone, «To God we belong and to him we shall return!» and he said:",
"footnotes": [
{
"id": 1650,
"documentId": "vo41n6tkvybr8p9w0qeae7bq",
"number": "831",
"section": "3.89",
"arabic_word": "",
"english_word": "said",
"arabic_interpretation": "",
"english_translation": "Qurʾan, Baqarah 2:156. The man is al-Ashʿath ibn Qays, to whom ʿAlī was offering condolences at the death of his brother, ʿAbd al-Raḥmān (Ḥarrānī, Tuḥaf, 209). See also ʿAlī’s condolence to Ashʿath on his son’s death in §3.277, and for an unnamed relative in §3.385.",
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:49.065Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:49.065Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:49.096Z"
}
],
"paragraphs": []
},
{
"id": 6735,
"documentId": "wqtyx27pymt8ntyyt4iebn89",
"title": "وقال عليه السلام وقد مدحه قوم في وجهه اللّٰهمّ إنّك أعلم بي من نفسي وأنا أعلم بنفسي منهم اللّٰهمّ ٱجعلنا خيرًا ممّا يظنّون وٱغفر لنا ما لا يعلمون.",
"slug": "lord-you-know-me-better-than-i-know-myself-and-i-know-myself-better-than-others-know-me",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:36.330Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:36.330Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:36.341Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "Lord, you know me better than I know myself, and I know myself better than others know me. Lord, make me more virtuous than they think, and forgive those of my actions they don’t know.",
"type": "en"
}
],
"sermonNumber": "3.90",
"heading": "Lord, you know me better than I know myself, and I know myself better than others know me.",
"footnotes": [
{
"id": 1652,
"documentId": "tvhjz955qge014flbq4rd84q",
"number": "832",
"section": ""3.90"",
"arabic_word": "",
"english_word": "know",
"arabic_interpretation": "",
"english_translation": "Presumably in Kufa during ʿAlī’s caliphate, 35-40/656-661. Response when he was praised to his face (Māmaṭīrī, Nuzhah, 243-244). Similar final line in §1.191.3 (see note on context there).",
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:49.469Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:49.469Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:11:49.497Z"
}
],
"paragraphs": []
},
{
"id": 6737,
"documentId": "q11rr1qr0rid6pv9iurp7ih5",
"title": "وقال عليه السلام لا يستقيم قضاء الحوائج إلّا بثلاث بٱستصغارها لتعظم وبٱستكتامها لتظهر وبتعجيلها لتهنأ.",
"slug": "your-benefaction-becomes-perfect-only-when-you-add-three-more-actions",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:36.871Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:36.871Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:36.880Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "Your benefaction becomes perfect only when you add three more actions: when you deem your favors small, they become great, when you conceal them, they become clear, and when you expedite them, they are received with joy.",
"type": "en"
}
],
"sermonNumber": "3.91",
"heading": "Your benefaction becomes perfect only when you add three more actions:",
"footnotes": [],
"paragraphs": []
},
{
"id": 6739,
"documentId": "ym9qess4pxxs5w7dlh31yz2k",
"title": "وقال عليه السلام يأتي على الناس زمان لا يُقرَّب فيه إلّا الماحل ولا يُظَرَّف فيه إلّا الفاجر ولا يضعّف فيه إلّا المنصف. يَعُدّون الصدقة فيه غُرمًا وصلة الرحم مَنًّا والعبادة ٱستطالة على الناس. فعند ذلك يكون السلطان بمشورة الإماء وإمارة الصبيان وتدبير الخصيان.",
"slug": "an-age-is-coming-to-the-world-in-which-none-but-the-schemer-will-be-granted-intimacy",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:37.326Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:37.326Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:37.333Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "An age is coming to the world in which none but the schemer will be granted intimacy, none but the debauched will be considered witty, and none but the just will be deemed weak. People will regard charity a tax, gifts to relatives a favor, and God’s worship a means to self-glorification. At that time, power will be wielded through the counsel of concubines, the command of boys, and the governance of eunuchs.",
"type": "en"
}
],
"sermonNumber": "3.92",
"heading": "An age is coming to the world in which none but the schemer will be granted intimacy,",
"footnotes": [
{
"id": 646,
"documentId": "jkop1zbxj8w4pgv5fo8yu01u",
"number": "333",
"section": "3.92",
"arabic_word": "الخصيان",
"english_word": "",
"arabic_interpretation": "ن، ش، ي، ه، وأضيفت في م: كذا. أصل م: سقطت <وتدبير الخصيان>.",
"english_translation": "",
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:07:53.313Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:07:53.313Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:07:53.325Z"
}
],
"paragraphs": []
},
{
"id": 6741,
"documentId": "hvwt01oc0baddvnguqc9w352",
"title": "ورُؤي عليه إزارٌ خَلِق مرقوع فقيل له في ذلك فقال يخشع له القلب وتذلّ به النفس ويقتدي به المؤمنون.",
"slug": "al-was-seen-wearing-a-worn-and-patched-garment-and-when-someone-remarked-on-this-he-explained",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:37.783Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:37.783Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:37.793Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "ʿAlī was seen wearing a worn and patched garment, and when someone remarked on this, he explained: The heart bows to him and the soul prostrates before him—true believers will follow my practice.",
"type": "en"
}
],
"sermonNumber": "3.93",
"heading": "ʿAlī was seen wearing a worn and patched garment, and when someone remarked on this, he explained:",
"footnotes": [],
"paragraphs": []
},
{
"id": 6743,
"documentId": "kgkoidr4lv63bmwwzh0h1rzb",
"title": "وقال عليه السلام إنّ الدنيا والآخرة عدوّان متفاوتان وسبيلان مختلفان فمن أحبّ الدنيا وتوّلاها أبغض الآخرة وعاداها وهما بمنزلة المشرق والمغرب وماشٍ بينهما كلّما قرب من واحد بعد من الآخر وهما بعدُ ضَرّتان.",
"slug": "this-world-and-the-hereafter-are-mutual-enemies-and-divergent-paths-to-love-and-follow-this-world-is",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:38.254Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:38.254Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:38.269Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "This world and the hereafter are mutual enemies and divergent paths—to love and follow this world is to hate and reject the hereafter. The two are like East and West for the person who walks between them—the nearer he draws to one, the further he moves from the other. They are like two wives married to one man.",
"type": "en"
}
],
"sermonNumber": "3.94",
"heading": "This world and the hereafter are mutual enemies and divergent paths—to love and follow this world is to hate and reject the hereafter.",
"footnotes": [],
"paragraphs": []
},
{
"id": 6745,
"documentId": "j2lebuxtl82dt0onm0kq3icp",
"title": "وعن نَوف البِكاليّ قال رأيت أمير المؤمنين عليه السلام ذات ليلة وقد خرج من فراشه فنظر إلى النجوم فقال يا نوف أراقد أنت أم رامق قلت بل رامق يا أمير المؤمنين فقال يا نوف طوبى للزاهدين في الدنيا الراغبين في الآخرة أولئك قوم ٱتّخذوا الأرض بساطًا وترابها فراشًا وماءها طيبًا والقرآن شعارًا والدعاء دثارًا ثمّ قرضوا الدنيا قرضًا على منهاج المسيح. يا نوف إنّ داود عليه السلام قام في مثل هذه الساعة من الليل فقال <إنّها ساعة لا يدعو فيها عبد إلّا ٱستجيب له إلّا أن يكون عَشّارًا أو عَريفًا أو شُرطيًّا أو صاحب عَرطبة (وهي الطُّنبور) أو صاحب كوبة (وهي الطَّبل)>. وقد قيل أيضًا إنّ العرطبة الطبل والكوبة الطنبور.",
"slug": "to-nawf-al-bik-l-pious-counsel-david-and-jesus-as-exemplars",
"type": "Saying",
"availableTranslations": null,
"createdAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:38.731Z",
"updatedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:38.731Z",
"publishedAt": "2025-09-11T18:01:38.740Z",
"translations": [
{
"text": "Nawf al-Bikālī narrated this report, and he said: I saw the Commander of the Faithful one night as he rose from his bed, gazed at the stars, then said to me, “Nawf, are you asleep or awake?” “I’m awake, Commander of the Faithful,” I replied. ʿAlī then said to me: Nawf, blessed are those who reject worldliness and focus their desire on the hereafter! They take God’s earth for a carpet, its dust for a bed, its water for perfume, the Qurʾan as their garment, and prayer as their robe. They cut their bonds with the world as the Messiah did. Nawf, the Prophet David stepped outside at just such an hour, and said, <This is an hour when the prayer of any who prays will be answered, unless he is a tax collector, an appraiser, an enforcer, an oud player (that is, a lute player), or a percussionist (that is, a drummer).> Raḍī: Alternatively, it is said that ʿarṭabah, the first word of the last pair, means drum, and kūbah, the second word, means lute.",
"type": "en"
}
],
